## Installation
Balans requires Python 3.10+ and can be installed from PyPI using `pip install balans`.

* In principle, Balans is MIP solver-agnostic.
* In practice, Balans is tested with the open-source `SCIP` solver and the commercial `Gurobi` solver.
* By default, Balans uses `SCIP`, equivalent to initialization with `Balans(mip_solver="scip")`
* Assuming a valid Gurobi license, Balans can also be initialized with `Balans(mip_solver="gurobi")`.


## Installation from Source Code
```
git clone https://github.com/skadio/balans.git
cd balans
pip install setuptools wheel # if wheel is not installed
python setup.py sdist bdist_wheel
pip install dist/balans-X.X.X-py3-none-any.whl
```

## Test Your Setup
```
$ git clone https://github.com/skadio/balans.git
$ cd balans
$ python -m unittest discover tests
```